 About ping 
 Helps in determining  TCP/IP   networks   IP  address as well as determine issues with the network and assists in resolving them. See the  ping  definition for a full description. 
 Availability 
 The ping command is an  external command  that is available in the below Microsoft operating systems as ping.exe. 
 Windows 95 Windows 98 Windows ME Windows NT Windows 2000 Windows XP Windows Vista Windows 7 Windows 8 Windows 10 
 Ping syntax 
 
 Windows Vista, 7, and 8 syntax 
 Windows XP and lower syntax 
 
 Windows Vista, 7, and 8 syntax 
 Usage: ping [-t] [-a] [-n count] [-l size] [-f] [-i TTL] [-v TOS] [-r count] [-s count] [[-j host-list] | [-k host-list]] [-